  <prompt>
    Replace the hardcoded GUID at `MatterPreFillService.cs:43-44` with a stable-code lookup via `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync(WorkspaceOptions.MatterPreFillPlaybookCode, tenantId)`. Per Pattern A, the typed option is already pre-added in task 013, so this migration only modifies `MatterPreFillService.cs` + its tests — no `WorkspaceOptions.cs` edit needed. NFR-07 BINDING: do NOT modify the pre-fill flow signature, `useAiPrefill` consumer, 45s timeout, or `$choices` output contract.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in pre-fill orchestration + NFR-07 binding invariants.</role>

  <goal>
    `MatterPreFillService.cs` resolves the pre-fill playbook via `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync(options.MatterPreFillPlaybookCode, tenantId)`. The hardcoded GUID is removed. The pre-fill flow signature, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill` consumer, and `$choices` output schema are unchanged. Unit tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/` updated to use stable code. Integration test for matter pre-fill end-to-end passes.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-02 + §1.7 Pattern A + NFR-07. `MatterPreFillService.cs:43-44` carries the hardcoded GUID for the matter pre-fill playbook. Pattern A migration shape: inject `IOptions&lt;WorkspaceOptions&gt;`, read `MatterPreFillPlaybookCode` (added in task 013), call `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync()`. The service's PUBLIC contract (method signature, timeout, output shape consumed by `useAiPrefill`) is BINDING — must remain unchanged.
    </background>
